{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nEditing a prompt's TEXT from the visual editor is ALREADY DELIVERED (story 6592 — \"Editor prompt library + authoring/write-back\", closed under epic da27): the prompt library can create + edit prompt text in place with atomic write-back and derived-index regen. What is still surfaced READ-ONLY and has NO recorded design is editing a step's CONTRACT (a prompt's front-matter `inputs`/`outputs` schema NAMES, and the scripted-op contract that lives in code). This ticket is now narrowed to BRAINSTORM/DESIGN the contract-editing question only.\n\n## What (to explore — not yet decided)\n- Editing a PROMPT's contract (front-matter `inputs`/`outputs` schema names) from the editor: how to pick/validate a registry schema; what happens to overrides (the override-drift gate); breaking-change UX for existing consumers.\n- The scripted-op (Python `@register_step`) contract boundary: can/should op contracts ever be editable from the editor? (almost certainly NO — code is the source) — document the boundary explicitly and why.\n- Provenance + safety: content hashes, readers-before-writers `schema_version` policy, refusing edits that would fork a shared prompt or silently break consumers.\n\n## Scope\nIn: a short design doc / ADR (options + tradeoffs + recommendation) for editing prompt CONTRACTS from the editor, plus the explicit op-contract-in-code boundary decision. Out: prompt-text editing (done via 6592); implementation (its own follow-on stories); changing the op-contract-in-code model.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A short design doc / ADR captures the contract-editing options above with tradeoffs and a recommended approach.\n- [ ] The decision states explicitly whether scripted-op contracts are editable from the editor (and why), and how prompt-contract editing preserves single-source-of-truth, the derived index, content-hash provenance, and the override-drift gate.\n- [ ] Notes prompt-TEXT editing as already delivered (story 6592); follow-on implementation stories are identified from the chosen approach.","title":"Brainstorm: allow editing a prompt CONTRACT from the visual editor (prompt-text editing shipped via 6592)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782780881435295001,"uuid":"e92ed75b-2c81-4849-ad2f-4aa97a972907"}